      <div class="article-teaser">
        Using contactless or an Oyster card to pay as you go for your travel is easy and flexible
        
      </div>
    
    
      <p>You can add money to an Oyster card or use contactless (card or device) straight away.</p>

<p>You only pay for the journeys you make and it's cheaper than buying a <a href="/fares/how-to-pay-and-where-to-buy-tickets-and-oyster/single-and-return-tickets">paper single or return ticket</a> (train companies may offer special deals on some journeys).</p>

<p>In Zones 1-9, your fare is <a href="/fares/find-fares/tube-and-rail-fares/pay-as-you-go-caps">capped</a> so you can travel as much as you like in one day or week (Monday to Sunday), without paying more.</p>

<p>You can only use contactless to pay as you go on TfL Rail to or from Reading to Iver. Journeys to or from these stations aren't included in caps.</p>
      
           
      
